On windows-open putty and login to the linux machine with ec2-user and password as redhat
make sure you are logged in with root. if not run, sudo su -
execute the following
mkdir .kube
cd .kube
run wget command given on teams chat and check whether the config file is downloaded or not by executing "ls" command
ls
mv index.html config
ls

execute the following
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
ls
mv kubectl /bin
chmod o+x /bin/kubectl
kubectl get nodes 

if above command is running raise your hands


=========================================
Exercise of basic command
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get ns
kubectl get nodes -o wide
kubectl get nodes --show-labels
kubectl describe node <nodename>
### you can get the nodename from kubectl get nodes command and do not write the greater than and less than signs.
kubectl get node <nodename> -o yaml
kubectl get node <nodename> -o yaml > node.yaml
vim node.yaml
see the files try to understand it and close it than

kubectl get ns
kubectl get all -n kube-system -o wide
check whether scheduler,controller,apiserver,etcd running on master or not.

kubectl create ns <yourname>
kubectl get ns   === your name should be the namespace name and it should be present over here, if yes, raise yourhand

kubectl api-resources === to see all the apiresources available at that time in kubernetes
====================================================
Pod exercise ---
kubectl get ns
Make sure you have namespace of your name than start

vim pod.yaml
======================================
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
        name: apachepod
        namespace: <username of yours>
        labels:
                env: prod
                app: apache
spec:
        containers:
                - name: firstcontainer
                  image: quay.io/kushalsamota/httpd
                  
=====================================
kubectl create -f pod.yaml -n <username of yours>
kubectl get pods <username of yours>
kubectl get pods -o wide <username of yours>
kubectl get pods --show-labels <username of yours>
kubectl describe pod apachepod <username of yours>
kubectl get pod apachepod -o yaml > pod1.yaml <username of yours>
vim pod1.yaml 
exit from file
kubectl delete pod apachepod <username of yours>
kubectl get pods <username of yours>

#########################################################
vim pod.yaml
===========================================
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
        name: apachepod
        namespace: <username of yours>
        labels:
                env: prod
                app: apache
spec:
        containers:
                - name: firstcontainer
                  image: quay.io/kushalsamota/httpd
                - name: secondcontainer
                  image: quay.io/kushalsamota/mysql
                  env:
                          - name: MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD
                            value: redhat
==============================================
save the file

kubectl create -f pod.yaml <username of yours>
kubectl get pods <username of yours> === two container will be running in a pod
kubectl get pods -o wide <username of yours>
kubectl describe pod apachepod <username of yours>
kubectl exec -it apachepod -c secondcontainer bash <username of yours>
exit
kubectl logs apachepod -c firstcontainer <username of yours>
kubectl logs apachepod -c secondcontainer <username of yours>
kubectl delete pod apachepod <username of yours>
kubectl get pods <username of yours>

##################################################
vim pod.yaml
=============================================
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
        name: apachepod
        namespace: <username of yours>
        labels:
                env: prod
                app: apache
spec:
        volumes:
                - name: myvol
                  emptyDir: {}
        containers:
                - name: firstcontainer
                  image: quay.io/kushalsamota/httpd
                  volumeMounts:
                          - name: myvol
                            mountPath: /usr/lkubectlal/apache2/htdkubectls
========================================
kubectl create -f pod.yaml <username of yours>
kubectl get pods <username of yours>
kubectl describe pod apachepod <username of yours>
kubectl delete pod apachepod <username of yours>

